groups.name: Administrators
groups.description: Administrators have complete and unrestricted access to the computer/domain

groups.name: Users
groups.description: Users are prevented from making accidental or intentional system-wide changes and can run most applications

groups.name: Guests
groups.description: Guests have the same access as members of the Users group by default, except for the Guest account which is further restricted

groups.name: Print Operators
groups.description: Members can administer printers installed on domain controllers

groups.name: Backup Operators
groups.description: Backup Operators can override security restrictions for the sole purpose of backing up or restoring files

groups.name: Replicator
groups.description: Supports file replication in a domain

groups.name: Remote Desktop Users
groups.description: Members in this group are granted the right to logon remotely

groups.name: Network Configuration Operators
groups.description: Members in this group can have some administrative privileges to manage configuration of networking features

groups.name: Performance Monitor Users
groups.description: Members of this group can access performance counter data locally and remotely

groups.name: Performance Log Users
groups.description: Members of this group may schedule logging of performance counters, enable trace providers, and collect event traces both locally and via remote access to this computer

groups.name: Distributed COM Users
groups.description: Members are allowed to launch, activate and use Distributed COM objects on this machine.

groups.name: IIS_IUSRS
groups.description: Built-in group used by Internet Information Services.

groups.name: Cryptographic Operators
groups.description: Members are authorized to perform cryptographic operations.

groups.name: Event Log Readers
groups.description: Members of this group can read event logs from local machine

groups.name: Certificate Service DCOM Access
groups.description: Members of this group are allowed to connect to Certification Authorities in the enterprise

groups.name: RDS Remote Access Servers
groups.description: Servers in this group enable users of RemoteApp programs and personal virtual desktops access to these resources. In Internet-facing deployments, these servers are typically deployed in an edge network. This group needs to be populated on servers running RD Connection Broker. RD Gateway servers and RD Web Access servers used in the deployment need to be in this group.

groups.name: RDS Endpoint Servers
groups.description: Servers in this group run virtual machines and host sessions where users RemoteApp programs and personal virtual desktops run. This group needs to be populated on servers running RD Connection Broker. RD Session Host servers and RD Virtualization Host servers used in the deployment need to be in this group.

groups.name: RDS Management Servers
groups.description: Servers in this group can perform routine administrative actions on servers running Remote Desktop Services. This group needs to be populated on all servers in a Remote Desktop Services deployment. The servers running the RDS Central Management service must be included in this group.

groups.name: Hyper-V Administrators
groups.description: Members of this group have complete and unrestricted access to all features of Hyper-V.

groups.name: Access Control Assistance Operators
groups.description: Members of this group can remotely query authorization attributes and permissions for resources on this computer.

groups.name: Remote Management Users
groups.description: Members of this group can access WMI resources over management protocols (such as WS-Management via the Windows Remote Management service). This applies only to WMI namespaces that grant access to the user.

groups.name: Storage Replica Administrators
groups.description: Members of this group have complete and unrestricted access to all features of Storage Replica.

groups.name: Domain Computers
groups.description: All workstations and servers joined to the domain

groups.name: Domain Controllers
groups.description: All domain controllers in the domain

groups.name: Schema Admins
groups.description: Designated administrators of the schema

groups.name: Enterprise Admins
groups.description: Designated administrators of the enterprise

groups.name: Cert Publishers
groups.description: Members of this group are permitted to publish certificates to the directory

groups.name: Domain Admins
groups.description: Designated administrators of the domain

groups.name: Domain Users
groups.description: All domain users

groups.name: Domain Guests
groups.description: All domain guests

groups.name: Group Policy Creator Owners
groups.description: Members in this group can modify group policy for the domain

groups.name: RAS and IAS Servers
groups.description: Servers in this group can access remote access properties of users

groups.name: Server Operators
groups.description: Members can administer domain servers

groups.name: Account Operators
groups.description: Members can administer domain user and group accounts

groups.name: Pre-Windows 2000 Compatible Access
groups.description: A backward compatibility group which allows read access on all users and groups in the domain

groups.name: Incoming Forest Trust Builders
groups.description: Members of this group can create incoming, one-way trusts to this forest

groups.name: Windows Authorization Access Group
groups.description: Members of this group have access to the computed tokenGroupsGlobalAndUniversal attribute on User objects

groups.name: Terminal Server License Servers
groups.description: Members of this group can update user accounts in Active Directory with information about license issuance, for the purpose of tracking and reporting TS Per User CAL usage

groups.name: Allowed RODC Password Replication Group
groups.description: Members in this group can have their passwords replicated to all read-only domain controllers in the domain

groups.name: Denied RODC Password Replication Group
groups.description: Members in this group cannot have their passwords replicated to any read-only domain controllers in the domain

groups.name: Read-only Domain Controllers
groups.description: Members of this group are Read-Only Domain Controllers in the domain

groups.name: Enterprise Read-only Domain Controllers
groups.description: Members of this group are Read-Only Domain Controllers in the enterprise

groups.name: Cloneable Domain Controllers
groups.description: Members of this group that are domain controllers may be cloned.

groups.name: Protected Users
groups.description: Members of this group are afforded additional protections against authentication security threats. See http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=298939 for more information.

groups.name: Key Admins
groups.description: Members of this group can perform administrative actions on key objects within the domain.

groups.name: Enterprise Key Admins
groups.description: Members of this group can perform administrative actions on key objects within the forest.

groups.name: DnsAdmins
groups.description: DNS Administrators Group

groups.name: DnsUpdateProxy
groups.description: DNS clients who are permitted to perform dynamic updates on behalf of some other clients (such as DHCP servers).
